records.addlTxt:
Defendant Lorenzo L Parker in court with attorney Parker Charles Mathers.  Defendant Lorenzo L Parker in custody.  Zachary A. Wittchow appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 2 YEARS, CONSECUTIVE with any other sentence, with credit for 236  DAYS time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 12 MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 12 MONTHS.  The defendant IS NOT ELIGIBLE for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program and IS NOT ELIGIBLE for the Challenge Incarceration Program. 

The Court imposed the following conditions of extended supervision:  

- AODA assessment and comply with any recommended treatment.
- No possession or use of any controlled substances without a valid prescription, with random drug tests.  Defendant shall be tested twice per month, randomly.  
- Seek and maintain full time employment.
- No association with known drug users or dealers, and no contact at any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packaged, or distributed.
- Court ordered defendant to provide a DNA sample, and to pay all MANDATORY COURT costs, fees, assessments, and surcharges through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Defendant to serve 10 days in the HOC, consecutive, for failure to pay.
- Pay all supervision fees.  Defendant to make regular payments.


Court advised defendant of his right to seek postconviction relief.
